generateSenses

public java.util.List<Sense> generateSenses(java.util.Set<net.sf.extjwnl.data.Word> lexemeGroup)
Deprecated. use generateSenses(Set, LexicalEntry) instead

This method consumes a Set of lexemes and generates a list of Senses.
Every Sense in the returned list is associated with one lexeme in the consumed Set.

Parameters:
lexemeGroup - a group of lexemes with equal lemma and part of speech
Returns:
list of Sense-instances, based on the consumed group of lexemes
See Also:
Word

generateSenses

public java.util.List<Sense> generateSenses(java.util.Set<net.sf.extjwnl.data.Word> lexemeGroup,
                                            LexicalEntry lexicalEntry)
This method consumes a Set of lexemes and generates a list of Senses.
Every Sense in the returned list is associated with one lexeme in the consumed Set.

Parameters:
lexemeGroup - a group of lexemes with equal lemma and part of speech
lexicalEntry - a LexicalEntry instance that contains generated Senses.
Returns:
list of Sense-instances, based on the consumed group of lexemes
